"0165369.xml"}, "text": "1997/98 only to be taken into account against proof (list of annexes)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For this purpose, it is generally sufficient if the following information is provided: Exact description of the asset; acquisition or manufacturing time; acquisition or manufacturing costs (if applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "with a corresponding note, provided the amounts are estimated); useful life acc"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "official"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Depreciation table at the time of acquisition or production; book value of the asset at the end of the 1996/97 financial year (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "taking into account asserted special depreciation); depreciation in the financial year; part of depreciation attributable to agricultural use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For assets acquired or manufactured after June 30, 1995 in the \"tobacco growing\" industry and after June 30, 1996 in the \"agriculture and animal breeding\" industry, the normal useful life is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Official depreciation table of the BMF No. 1 BStBl 1996 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "3 and no.2 BStBl 1996 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1416 decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the cases affected here, there are basically no concerns about this depreciation table also for before 1 7 1995 or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1 7 to apply assets purchased or manufactured in 1996"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If the farmer and forester asserts AfA from the acquisition or manufacture of assets from past assessment periods, these can only be taken into account if he can prove or at least credibly demonstrate the acquisition or manufacture of assets with the corresponding expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A further estimate of depreciation will be omitted from FY"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1997/98"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the past, expenses for low-value assets were taken into account in full as immediately deductible operating expenses when determining the initial estimated amount and the material construction costs in tobacco production in the year of acquisition or manufacture"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Depreciation for such assets can therefore not (additionally) be deducted as business expenses in later financial years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "I ask, farmers and foresters, for whom the estimated starting amounts or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "the reference amount for the actual building costs were set, within the scope of the ongoing assessment work on the from Wj"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1997/98 changed determination of the profit and to point out the submission of an annex"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "I have no concerns if the above statements are adopted in whole or in part"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "224 sales guide values \u200b\u200bSales guide values \u200b\u200bper ha / LP for the year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "19961 2 3 41 42 5Classification into the groupsGrain cultivationHead crop cultivationDairy cattleFodder cultivation (35 dairy) cows35 dairy cows DM DM DM DM DM DM Sales 3300 4000 9900 2700 4500 3900 Surcharge for early potatoes not applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Additional profits231 Viticulture, fruit and vegetable cultivation The determination of the profit from viticulture or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Fruit and vegetable growing is according to the instructions in the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "from 7 10 1997 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - and from 9 1 1998 - S-2233 A - St 34 2 - to be carried out"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "232 Tobacco growing According to the determinations made, the crop yields in the Palatinate cultivation area have developed as follows (1 dt = 100 kg): Total cultivation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Price DM / dt net (+) Income net (+) 1994/95 1037 23731 168991472288 712 16293 1995/96934 22796 15985620 2441 701 17117 1996/97919 25630 18316038 2790 715 19938Geudertheimer (cigar goods) 1994/95 648 15132 10022873 2337 66 96618 15148 9873092 2450 652 15972 1996/97629 17595 11794315 2798 670 18752 Burley (cutting material) 1994/95 312 7083 5611694 2266 792 179541995/96236 5777 4563357 2449 790 19345 1996/97207 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 6070 4921022 2931 811 23758 670 4921022 2931 811 23758 / 9680 1871 1549 171 2443 828 19401 1996/9783 1965 1600 701 2379 815 19381 (+) incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Main premium and special aid paid from 1993/94 The tobacco vintage 1996 was of above-average quality and good quality"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the tobacco growing area Wittlich the quality was below average due to growth damage"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In 1996, hail damage occurred in almost all tobacco-growing areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "There were total failures from Herxheim to H\u00f6rdt and locally in the communities of Otterstadt and M\u00f6rlheim"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The community of Kandel was spared from damage by hail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Due to the membership in the producer group for tobacco growers in Rhineland-Palatinate, every tobacco grower has the right to receive a special subsidy, which is to be recorded as operating income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The income from hail insurance compensation is not included in the table"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "To compensate for the actual building costs, in Wj"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1996/97 - as before - 8,900 DM per hectare of cultivated area are taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "To estimate the actual building costs from Wj"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1997/98 see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "2233 Retirement benefits / pension benefits31 General information on non-cash retirement benefitsIncible retirement benefits are deductible at their actual value, which must be proven in detail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If an individual record is not provided, the value of non-cash partial retirement benefits is to be estimated in accordance with Section 1 (1) of the SachBezV in the version applicable for the respective assessment period (BFH rulings of 23 May 1989 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "784 and from 18 12 1990 BStBl 1991 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "354 and H 87 (partial retirement benefit) EStH 1996)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For the age-sharing spouse, only 80%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "to take this value into account (Section 1 (4) SachBezV)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "32 Value of non-cash retirement benefits The following is a list of the non-objection limits, which are determined in accordance with Section 1 (1) SachBezV in the version applicable for the respective assessment period: 1996 1997 (BStBl 1995 I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "820) (BStBl 1996 I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1556) Meals, heating and lighting, Meals, heating and lighting, DM DM DM DM, single person 4152 923 4212 937, couple 7474 1661 7582 1687 The values \u200b\u200bfor heating and lighting were estimated on the basis of the values \u200b\u200bvalid for 1994, taking into account inflationary surcharges, as there are no corresponding stipulations in the SachBezV (\u00a7\u00a7\u00a7 3 4 para 2 SachBezV 1995)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The non-objection limits do not apply if it is evident from the company's profit determination documents that the costs attributable to the retirees are lower"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "33 Extraordinary maintenance expenses as utility services 331 Maintenance expenses as subsidized utility services According to the BMF letter of 23 12 1996 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1508, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "30 and 34 (corresponds to FM decree of 23 12 1996 - S-2257 A - 442 -; ESt-Kartei: card 12 to \u00a7 22 EStG), maintenance expenses represent a supply service if they are paid to the transferor of assets as a contribution in kind (see also BFH- Judgment of 25 3 1992 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1012)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The transferee must therefore free the sender of a debt with the maintenance measures"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "332 Extraordinary maintenance expenses in connection with an agreed right of usufruct Since according to the civil law principles (\u00a7 1041 BGB) the owner has to bear the extraordinary expenses, he cannot release the asset sender and usufructuary (insofar) from a debt that encumbles him"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "There are therefore no supply services with regard to (extraordinary) maintenance expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "All maintenance expenses incurred by the owner in accordance with Section 1041 of the German Civil Code (BGB) cannot be taken into account as supply services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "At the usufructuary or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Recipients of agreed pension benefits are accordingly not receiving any other income (see BMF letter of 23 12 1996 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", with reference to the BFH judgment of 26 7 1995 BStBl 1996 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "157)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to \u00a7 1041 BGB, the usufructuary only has to bear the normal maintenance costs because he is only entitled to the normal uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The usual maintenance measures include all that are necessary after the course of things from time to time, namely at shorter intervals, so that the thing retains its quality when ordering usufruct (see Petzoldt in: Munich Commentary on the BGB, \u00a7 1041 margin no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "As a result, only cosmetic repairs and smaller, ongoing repairs (maintenance expenses) come into consideration as supply services"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "333 Maintenance expenses in connection with an agreed right of residence For the granting of a real or compulsory right of residence, the above applies accordingly in accordance with Section 1093 (1) BGB"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "34 Sufficiently profitable economic entity when transferring an agricultural and forestry business with profit determination according to \u00a7 13a EStGB when examining whether a sufficiently profitable economic entity (type 1) within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "11 of the BMF letter of 23 December 1996 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", are available, according to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "14 to determine the income on the basis of the taxable income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It is questionable whether, in the case of a transfer of an agricultural and forestry business with profit determination according to \u00a7 13a EStG, the resulting income is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "I ask you to take the view that the determination of profits according to \u00a7 13a EStG for those according to the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A determination to be made whether the income from a transferred agricultural and forestry operation is sufficient to provide the recurring services is unsuitable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In order to ensure an objective and approximate determination of the earning power of the transferred assets, it is therefore necessary to assign the transferred business entity to type 1 or type 2 (= economic entity securing a livelihood without sufficient income, see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "17 of the BMF letter of 23 December 1996 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") a change in the method of profit determination is required"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For income taxation, if the requirements of Section 13a (1) EStG are met, the determination of profits in accordance with Section 13a EStG is still decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If a corresponding profit determination is not made according to \u00a7 4 EStG, the transferred assets are to be assigned to type 2"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "35 Pension services in connection with an indirect property donation The object of the property transfer must according to the BMF letter of 23 12 1996 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", be an economic entity that at least partially secures the existence of the transferor of assets (BFH decision of 5 7 1990 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "847)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This follows from the civil law conception of the transfer of assets, namely moving up the following generations in living assets as the basis of one's own economic activity and the provision of the transferor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The transferred assets must be suitable and intended for a cross-generational permanent investment and be left to the transferee to continue the business in order to at least partially secure the existence of the transferor (BMF letter of 23 12 1996 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It is crucial that the property is handed over unchanged in its type and substance from the transferor to the property transferee for further management"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "With this approach, recurring services rendered by the recipient of the indirect property donation to the donor cannot, contrary to the view partly represented in the literature, not provide any pension services within the meaning of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "2 of the BMF letter of 23 December 1997 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", be"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 Intangible assets 41 Sugar beet delivery law 411 Independent intangible assets A sugar beet delivery law is an independent intangible asset that is independent of goodwill because it represents an asset that has a significant value for the company that extends beyond the duration of the individual tax section, can be assessed separately and can be obtained the taxpayer can pay something (BFH judgment of 19 6 1997 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "809)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It is irrelevant whether the right can be sold individually; the transfer together with the operation is sufficient (BFH judgment of 19 6 1997 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "412 For activation The delivery right (as fixed assets of the agricultural and forestry business) can only be activated if it was acquired against payment (Section 5 (2) EStG) or incorporated into business assets (R 3 a (2) and (3) sentence 4 EStR 1996 )"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "413 To wear and tear The right is not subject to wear and tear"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Although the quota system for sugar-producing companies that has existed throughout the EU since 1968 (the delivery rights of individual farmers and foresters is derived from this), a time limit has been provided from the start, but this has always been extended so far, so that according to the BFH ruling of 18 12 1970 BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "237 an unlimited regulation can be assumed for tax purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "414 Approval of a lower partial value In individual cases, the approach of the lower partial value according to Section 6 Paragraph 1 No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "1 of the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "from 15 10 1996 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 -)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Such an approach cannot be based on the BMF letter of 2 4 1996 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "372 (corresponds to FM decree of 12 3 1996 - S-2172 A - 442 -; ESt-Kartei: card 18 to \u00a7 6 Abs 1 Nr 1 EStG) for the partial value depreciation of long-distance freight transport licenses acquired against payment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The depreciation permitted there is due to the fact that the quotas were actually removed and the resulting drop in prices for such concessions"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In contrast, with regard to the quota system currently in place on the EU sugar market up to 2001, there is no decision on their removal of quotas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Furthermore, a drop in prices for sugar beet delivery rights in Rhineland-Palatinate cannot currently be determined"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "415 Uniform assets In the case of an applied for partial depreciation or a partial sale of an activated sugar beet delivery right, the following must also be observed: The rights acquired against payment and free of charge form a uniform asset"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "An approach of the lower partial value can therefore only be considered if the partial value of the entire delivery right of the agricultural and forestry enterprise falls below the capitalized acquisition costs"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If such a uniform delivery right is partially sold, only a portion corresponding to the share of the overall delivery right is to be taken into account as a book value reduction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "42 Milk production law 421 Independent intangible economic good Milk production law is also a uniform and independent intangible economic good that is to be assigned to the fixed assets of the agricultural and forestry business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "422 On wear and tear Although the milk quota regulation has already been extended several times since its introduction in 1984 (most recently until 31 3 2000) and there are no indications of when the production restrictions will expire, according to the administrative opinion (see BMF letter of 2 2 1995 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "148; corresponds to FM decree of 2 2 1995 - S-2132 A - 442 - and ESt-Kartei: card 18 f to \u00a7 13 EStG) with this right - in contrast to the above-mentioned delivery law - a time limit of 10 years can be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition costs for such a production right are therefore deductible evenly over its ten-year useful life in accordance with Section 7 (1) EStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, if a production right is acquired against payment in different financial years, each acquisition must be viewed in isolation, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "the acquisition costs of each acquired right are to be spread over the ten-year useful life"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "R 44 (11) EStR 1996 and H 44 (subsequent acquisition or production costs) EStH 1996 are not relevant in this case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "423 Approval of a lower partial value If a partial value depreciation is applied for on an activated production right or if such a right is partially sold, the above apply"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Principles of the sugar beet delivery law with the proviso that the book value reduced by the annual depreciation must be compared with the value of the entire milk production law"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "43 Approach of sugar beet delivery law and milk production law when the business is closed 431 Transfer to private assets If an effective task of the agricultural and forestry business is to be assumed and if this business has a sugar beet supply law or a milk production law, these intangible assets are transferred to private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to the constant rulings of the highest court (see BFH judgment of 4 4 1989 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "606) goodwill cannot be transferred to private assets, but this case law cannot be transferred to other - including intangible - economic assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "432 Approach of the common value In accordance with Section 16 (3) of the Income Tax Act, the common value of the aforementioned rights at the time of the abandonment must also be included in the profit from the business closure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The common value is determined in accordance with Section 9 (2) BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the price that would be achieved in normal business transactions according to the nature of the individual economic goods in the event of a sale is decisive"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "All price-determining factors must be taken into account, but not unusual or personal circumstances (BFH judgment of 2 3 1989 BFH / NV 1990 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "88)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "433 To determine the common value The common value of the sugar beet delivery law and the milk production law therefore corresponds to their market value (= purchase price) and can, according to established case law (see BFH judgment of 8 September 1994 BStBl 1995 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "309) are primarily derived from sales of such rights that were timely at the time of the valuation (= posting time)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the case of sales up to one year before or after the assessment date (see BFH judgment of 26 9 1980 BStBl 1981 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "153) can be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If there are no such sales, according to the BFH judgment of 8 9 1994 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Sales with a longer time interval to the valuation point are included in the valuation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If sales of the rights addressed here from the regional area of \u200b\u200ban affected farmer and forest manager are not known, sales from the supraregional area can also form essential and decisive clues in the valuation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to the BFH judgment of 12 12 1991 BStBl 1992 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "462 is not a value influencing factor and is therefore insignificant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Information on sales prices of milk production rights in Rhineland-Palatinate since 1994 can be obtained from OFD Koblenz (Dipl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "(FH) Erich Jung, Tel"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "No. 0261 493 1264) can be made available on request"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Their - currently still valid - time limit has so far had no effect on the value of the sugar beet delivery right and the milk production right"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The same applies with regard to the assumption made for milk production law that its value would be forfeited due to imminent changes in the milk quota"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "5 Demarcation of agriculture and forestry from trade51 General The principles for the demarcation of agriculture and forestry from trade result from R 135 EStR 1996 and H 135 EStH 1996 An overview of the most important (turnover) limits mentioned there is attached as Annex 1"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "52 Treatment or processing of our own agricultural and forestry products (R 135 Paragraph 3 EStR 1996) If our own agricultural and forestry products are only cleaned, preserved by preserving or deep freezing and packaged in commercially available portions, this does not affect the primary agricultural and forestry production exceeded because there is still no processing or processing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Agricultural and forestry products are still present even if they are on a so-called"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "first processing stage are processed or processed (= agricultural and forestry subsidiary) and come mainly from the own farm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The treatment or processing of predominantly third-party products and the treatment or processing of own agricultural and forestry products in the second processing stage is (apart from the simplification regulation in R 135 Paragraph 3 Sentence 2 EStR 1996; non-damaging sales of 20,000 DM for own products the second processing stage in the context of direct marketing) according to R 135 para 3 EStR 1996 as a commercial activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Annex 2 includes an exemplary overview of the tax assessment of the treatment or processing of a large number of agricultural and forestry products"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "53 Use of economic goods outside of the agricultural and forestry operations (R 135 Paragraph 9 EStR 1996) 531 Acquisition specifically for external use If the farmer and forestry manager provides services with economic goods (machines and devices) that he has acquired specifically for external use, this means that there is a commercial enterprise right from the start (R 135 para 9 sentence 1 EStR 1996 and BFH judgment of 23 1 1992 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "951)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In principle, this can be assumed if a special machine that is not customary, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Forest tractor in the pure agricultural operation or another similar machine, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Combine harvester or grape harvester, although the existing machinery is by far sufficient for the management of one's own business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This applies even if the economic goods purchased for the inter-company use of machines are used temporarily or occasionally in the company's own agricultural and forestry operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The simplification regulation in R 135 (9) sentence 3 EStR 1996 is irrelevant in this case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The above principles apply accordingly to leased assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "532 Reclassification of an asset If an asset is reclassified after a - possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "extending over years - internal use of the aforementioned (harmful) external use, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Acquisition of a new (second) grape harvester mainly for the company's own operations and the use of the old (first) for inter-company use, from the time of reallocation it can be assumed that it will be a commercial activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The decisive factor here is that when assessing whether the inter-company use of machines represents an agricultural, forestry or commercial activity, no viable reason is seen for deciding on the acquisition of the assets used in any other way than the reallocation of the goods that have been used in agriculture for years. and forestry operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "533 Unified commercial contracting company If a farmer and forester who, in addition to his agricultural and forestry business, also runs a commercial contracting company with not inconsiderable sales, uses economic goods from his agricultural and forestry business also for services in other agricultural and forestry operations, so is all A uniform business operation is required for external activities if the required organizational and actual separation between the areas of activity is missing"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Against an organizational and actual separation of the areas of activity speak z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The following indications: the farmer and forest manager addresses the same group of customers with his services; similar activities are carried out; the management of the inter-company activities is carried out from the same establishment; the same machines and equipment and / or employees are used in both areas of activity; the invoices are not clearly separated; there is a uniform set of bookkeeping; the income and expenses of both areas of activity are processed via the same account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If there is organizational separation of the areas of activity, there is nevertheless a uniform business operation to the extent that the activities performed for other farmers and foresters are comparable to those of the commercial contractor"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This is the case, for example, if the taxpayer operates a contracting company with a grape harvester and also uses the grape harvester from his agricultural and forestry operations in other agricultural and forestry operations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "534 Assignment of assets to agricultural and forestry or commercial business assets If the scope of commercial activity increases in such cases, it must also be checked whether the assets used outside the business can still be assigned to agricultural and forestry business assets or because they are predominantly used in commercial contractors must be allocated to the business assets of the business enterprise"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "54 Services of the farmer and forestry operator without the use of machines (R 135 Abs 10 EStR 1996)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "can only be assigned to his agricultural and forestry operation if it is a typical agricultural and forestry activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This only includes activities in the context of the direct agricultural and forestry production process, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Cultivating fields, harvesting, feeding and caring for cattle"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In contrast, haulage, landscape maintenance, slaughter and repair work, for example, are not typical agricultural and forestry activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "55 Demarcation issues relating to the accommodation of strangers (R 135 Paragraph 12 EStR 1996) 551 General According to R 135 Paragraph 12 EStR 1996, the demarcation of commercial operations compared to agriculture and forestry in the accommodation of strangers is based on the principles of R 137 EStR 1996; Particularly relevant are H 137 Paragraph 2 (holiday apartment), (guest house), (commercial nature of the rental activity) and (rental of furnished rooms) EStH 1996 The rental of holiday apartments and rooms and the related services are therefore commercial under the same conditions according to which even with a non-farmer a commercial use transfer, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "in the form of a hotel or a guesthouse"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "552 Permanent rental The permanent rental of furnished rooms is generally not a commercial activity if, in addition to the provision of use, the cleaning of the rooms, the provision of breakfast and the like are provided as an additional service (H 137 para 2 (rental of furnished rooms) EStH 1996 and BFH- Judgment of 11 7 1984 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "722)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "553 Temporary accommodation In contrast, accommodation in guest houses is always a commercial enterprise (H 137 para 2 (guest house) EStH 1996 with reference to the aforementioned BFH judgment of 11 7 1984 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the temporary accommodation of strangers in furnished guest rooms or apartments, this can also include the provision of such rooms or apartments for such use by farmers and foresters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For reasons of simplification, however, according to R 135 (12) sentence 2 EStR 1996, no commercial activity is to be assumed if fewer than four rooms or fewer than six beds are available to accommodate strangers and no main meal is allowed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Because the previously valid, linguistically differently worded simplification regulation (see Section 103 Paragraph 7 Sentence 2 of the Guidelines for Valuation of Agricultural and Forestry Assets and Section 264 Paragraph 3 Sentence 2 UStR 1996) should not be changed, the morning breakfast is, although In this respect - viewed in isolation - it is a commercial service, within the scope of the simplification regulation it is still not a - harmful - main meal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If the room or bed limit is exceeded, commercial use is not to be assumed in every case, but the nature of the activity based on the delimitation criteria listed in R 137 EStR 1996 and H 137 EStH 1996 - developed by case law - to be checked"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "554 Temporary accommodation with additional services However, the aforementioned simplification regulation does not apply if, in connection with the rental of rooms or apartments to holiday guests, additional, typical commercial services are provided to a not inconsiderable extent and a uniform overall activity can be assumed (BFH judgment of 21 December 1976 BStBl 1977 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "244 and BFH judgment of 28 6 1984 BStBl 1985 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "211)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In addition to the pure rental service, the following services are provided in some cases: provision of breakfast; provision of further meals; final cleaning of the rooms; provision of a common room, garden, children's playground accessible to all tenants; advice on the design of the stay, organizing excursions; taking phone calls; events for social get-togethers (barbecues etc.)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "); Provision of riding horses, bicycles, bed linen, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "; Keeping drinks and food ready (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Bread and milk service)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The mediation of tourist leisure offers alone is not sufficient for the assumption of a uniform commercial service (BFH judgment of 25 11 1988 BFH / NV 1990 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "36)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "555 Allocation to agricultural and forestry business assets If the accommodation of strangers by farmers and foresters mentioned here is not a commercial activity, there is income from agriculture and forestry if the leased premises belong to their - tolerated - business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, if such a rental and possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Together with a long-term apartment rental, the structure of the agricultural and forestry operation changes so decisively that it takes a backseat to this transfer of use, the rental assets are to be removed from the agricultural and forestry operation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "556 Accommodation activity by a partnership Pursuant to Section 15 (3) No. 1 EStG, the activity of a partnership is fully considered commercial if it also carries out a commercial activity"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the accommodation activity is of a commercial nature, the infection of this income as such from commercial operations by a partnership that otherwise operates in agriculture and forestry can be caused by outsourcing the commercial activity with the associated assets to a second, if necessary, from the start of use at the latest"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "partnership with the same participation can be prevented (see BMF letter of 13 5 1996 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "621; corresponds to FM decree of 13 5 1996 - S-2241 A - 442 - and ESt-Kartei: card 21 to \u00a7 15 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The same applies if this commercial activity is carried out by one or more partners of the agricultural and forestry partnership in rooms rented by this company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "6 Depreciation authorization of the legatee usufructuary in an agricultural and forestry business Up to now, an express regulation on the depreciation authorization of a legacy usufructuary has only existed for the area of \u200b\u200bincome from renting and leasing (No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "51 41 of the BMF letter of 15 11 1984 BStBl I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "561; corresponds to FM decree of 15 11 1984 - S-2253 A - 442 - and ESt-Kartei: card 18 a to \u00a7 21 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "With judgment of 28 9 1993 BStBl 1994 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "319, the BFH decided that a legacy usufructuary who earns income from renting and leasing is not entitled to the depreciation on the acquisition or production costs borne by the testator"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "With BMF letter of 22 4 1994 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "258 (corresponds to FM decree of 22 4 1994 - S-2253 A - 442 - and ESt-Kartei: card 18 f to \u00a7 21 EStG), a transitional regulation has been made for the legal principles of this judgment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For the operational area, these regulations for the depreciation authorization of a legacy usufructuary were applied accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "There is therefore no need for a separate transitional regulation for the application of the BFH judgment of 28 9 1995 BStBl 1996 II S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Basis: BMF letter dated 17 October 1997 - IV B 3 - S-2253 - 53/97 -7 Domestic study or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Office of a farmer and forestry manager71 Deduction restriction Even if the home office or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Office of a farmer and forestry manager is to be recognized for tax purposes in principle, the deduction restriction for such expenses standardized in Section 4 (5) sentence 1 No. 6 b EStG from 1 1 1996 must be observed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For the decision in what amount the expenses for a home office or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "an office can be deducted as business expenses, it is fundamentally irrelevant whether the home office is also a business premises within the meaning of \u00a7 12 AO or belongs to the - necessary - (special) business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "An unlimited deduction for such expenses is only permitted if the home office is the focus of all operational and professional activities"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The fulfillment of these constituent elements requires u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It is assumed that the taxpayer does not work permanently outside the office - even if it is in different places (see BMF letter of 22 1 1998 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "129, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "8th; corresponds to the ESt card index: card 5 to Section 4 (5) and (6) EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, this is precisely not the case with the farming and forestry manager"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, the farmer or forester can spend expenses for his home office or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "his office in the works manager's apartment is basically only up to DM 2,400 in the fiscal year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "deduct as business expenses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "72 Allocation to business assets Irrespective of the extent of the allowable deduction of expenses according to \u00a7 4 Paragraph 5 Clause 1 No. 6 b EStG, the allocation of the room (s) used by the farmer and forest manager for exclusively or at least predominantly operational purposes to business assets must be assessed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Because the above-mentioned deduction restriction has no influence on this, it is - as before - an independent (self-employed) part of the building that always belongs to the necessary (special) business assets, unless the requirements for the acceptance of a piece of property of subordinate value are not met are"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "8 Extent of the land belonging to the apartment i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "of Section 52 (15) of the Income Tax Act81 Decision by the income tax officers of the highest federal and state tax authorities After a decision by the income tax officers of the highest federal and state financial authorities, the following applies to the conditions set out in no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 of the BMF letter of 4 6 1997 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "630 (corresponds to ESt-Kartei: Map 4 to \u00a7 13 EStG) contains the following indefinite legal terms: 811 Pick-up limit of 1000 sqm The possibility of a tax-free withdrawal is not limited to 1000 sqm for garden areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The in the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of 4 6 1997 cited 1000 square meters according to the wording of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 expressly represents a limit of coverage that serves to simplify administration"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, a tax-free withdrawal is also possible in cases that exceed 1000 square meters, provided that the requirements of No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 are completely fulfilled"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "812 Slightly exceeding the limit of exposure According to the general principles, jurisdiction, literature and administration consider a volume of up to 10% as \"minor\""}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "viewed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Consequently, with a limit of 1000 sqm, this leads to a case-by-case examination for garden areas over 1100 sqm"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "813 Necessity of garden areas The necessity is primarily based on objective criteria, such as"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Apartment and company size, but not based on marital status or the number of people in the household, etc."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "to eat"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "814 Usual size of garden areas According to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter dated June 4, 1997, the local conditions in agricultural residential buildings must be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This regulation is intended to explicitly take into account the special features of garden areas in agricultural residential buildings as opposed to single-family houses (especially row houses)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "815 Foreseeable time based on Section 69 (1) BewG and the relevant case law (see BFH judgment of 18 7 1989 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "744) as well as with reference to Section 2 Paragraph 7 BewR Gr and \u00a7 4 WertV, the term \"in the foreseeable future\" should be understood to mean a period of about six years"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "is viewed as building land, industrial land or land for transport purposes, as an indication of the imminent cessation of use as a garden area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "816 clues for the future discontinuation of the use as garden area This regulation has the consequence that the local tax authorities cannot simply take over the declared allocation of garden areas to the apartment, but have to check specifically whether there is a tax-free removable garden area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "82 Effects of the value-in-use taxation 821 Value-in-use taxation still to be carried out As long as the value-in-use taxation pursuant to Section 52 (15) sentences 2 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "EStG is to be carried out for an apartment, all parts of the property used by the taxpayer in direct or indirect connection with this apartment (regardless of the size of the area and the cadastral parcel designation) are to be assigned to the (agricultural and forestry) business assets (the living of the farmer and forester is operational caused as long as the value in use taxation applies)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "822 Loss of value-in-use taxation Only when the value-in-use taxation for the apartment ceases to apply, all of the privately used properties and parts of the property must be transferred to private assets (R 13, Paragraph 9, Clause 1 and R 14, Paragraph 3, Clause 4 EStR 1996)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The withdrawal profit remains after the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of June 4, 1997, only with regard to the areas required and customary for (private) residential use, excepted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The privately used parts of the land that also belong to the apartment are taxable from the business assets at the time at which a value in use is recognized for the last time"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The application for the elimination of the value-in-use taxation for a previous VZ is a retroactive event according"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Section 175 (1) sentence 1 no.2 AO"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "83 Parts of the land belonging to the apartment 831 Entrances, driveways and parking spaces Areas that are not exclusively or almost exclusively (i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "to more than 90 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") are related to the residential building (apartment), but to at least 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "also serve other purposes cannot be regarded as land belonging to the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "These areas include entrances, driveways and parking spaces that are not only used exclusively for the residential building (apartment), e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "shared access or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Access to residential and farm buildings, yard and maneuvering room, parking space for machines and devices or company cars"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "With an operational use of at least 50%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, it concerns necessary business assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "832 Garden areas House gardens, the products of which are also sold to third parties, continue to count as land that does not belong to the apartment (cf. the minutes of the income tax group meeting of August 22, 1988 - S-2319 A - St 31 1 -, Part V no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Ornamental areas that have no recognizable direct connection to the apartment, but rather give the entire courtyard the required design, are not to be added to the necessary private assets even after the value-in-use taxation for a farm manager's apartment or senior citizen apartment has ceased and therefore to be left in the business assets without the taxpayer's express withdrawal action"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This also applies in particular to larger park-like facilities on the farm, existing or unused, for example overgrown, or only temporarily or occasionally privately used areas with trees that can be used for forestry purposes"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Areas that are not spatially related to the residential building, even when used as an ornamental or house garden, are not land belonging to the apartment (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "and BMF letter of 4 June 1997 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This can be the case, for example, for an area on the other side of the street"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, this does not apply if this is the only garden of the farmer and forestryman (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "of up to 1000 square meters in size), which is at least 90 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "is used privately and is therefore clearly related to the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Example: The land of a courtyard property and a plot of land in the vicinity over a total of 3000 square meters are to be assigned as follows, taking into account the uses listed below: Uses Total area Land belonging to the apartment Land not belonging to the apartment Built-up area of \u200b\u200bthe residential building incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Wrap around 250 sqm 250 sqm covered area of \u200b\u200bthe farm building incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Wrap around 800 sqm 800 sqm separate entrance to the residential building 50 sqm 50 sqm common driveway and courtyard area (serves more than 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "operational purposes) 150 sqm 150 sqm ornamental and vegetable garden (exclusively used privately) 800 sqm 800 sqm fallow area 500 sqm 500 sqm house garden (independent property without close spatial relationship to the apartment) 450 sqm 450 sqm total 3000 sqm 1100 sqm 1900 sqm On the question of the extent of the Areas belonging to an apartment can be taken tax-free, see below under no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "84833 Situation at the time of removal The extent of the land belonging to the apartment is generally based on the actual circumstances at the time of removal"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Only those property areas can be assigned to the apartment whose private use is permanent at the time of extraction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, the farmer and forester can basically the decision-relevant facts, z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "whether a partial area is exclusively private or at least 10%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "is used operationally, sometimes design it yourself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In particular if the tax office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If the facts ascertained during a site inspection deviate from the declared one or if there is no agreement, the facts and the reason for the disputed assessment must be put on record in detail"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "As far as factual questions are concerned in such a starting position, I ask for reasons of legal certainty to ask the taxpayer to provide written explanations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "On factual issues that are relevant to the decision, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "An actual agreement can also be sought about the type, scope and duration of a property use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "84 On the scope of the associated land that can be obtained tax-free 841 On the limit of collection According to the administrative opinion (see under No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "811) in individual cases (exceptionally) the tax-free garden area can be more than 1000 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, it cannot be inferred from this that there is a fundamental right to a tax-free withdrawal of at least 1000 square meters of the land belonging to the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If the area designated and used by the taxpayer as a garden does not exceed 1000 square meters, according to the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of 4 6 1997 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 as a rule, the declared allocation to the apartment must be followed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In particular, if the specified area contains a parceled and therefore marketable property or a partial area is buildable due to the location and layout of the property, the simplification rule does not apply (no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 last sentence)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "842 Required and customary areas for private residential use Independent and marketable plots of land used as garden areas, which meet the criteria as accessory areas but can be built on independently, are no longer in the necessary close connection with the dwelling because of the possible future use as building land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "4 of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter dated June 4, 1997, the permissible tax-free withdrawal only includes the areas required and customary for private use of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Their possible future use must also be taken into account"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Can according to the spatial conditions (possibly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "together with partial areas of an adjacent parcel of the Stpfl) partial areas of a parcel of another use (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "by inclusion in the development plan as building land or by development in the unplanned interior area according to \u00a7 34 BauGB), a tax-free withdrawal is also not possible even if this area could actually be regarded as a customary accessory area according to the aforementioned principles and the area for agricultural use Residential building not reached usual size"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Otherwise, the question of necessity can only be determined in individual cases as part of an overall assessment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The following speaks for the necessity, for example: The garden areas are only accessible from the residential building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A future agricultural use or development of partial areas is unlikely due to the location of the areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Residential use would be more than slightly restricted if parts of the area were not part of the apartment"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It can be assumed that a potential purchaser who only wants to acquire the residential building would not acquire this building without these garden areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A partial area remaining after deducting a required amount could no longer be used independently of the apartment and in particular by third parties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The following speaks against the necessity, for example: A partial area remaining after deducting a required amount could represent a marketable building plot"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The garden area is accessed from a street"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Another use of partial areas (building land, industrial land or land for transport purposes) is possible in the foreseeable future (around six years)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The garden area is used by other buildings in the yard as a shoulder, spacing area, access road or storage area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Partial areas are not occupied directly on the residential building"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The characteristic of the usual size of garden areas is to be assessed according to the local conditions in agricultural residential buildings (as opposed to single-family houses - especially terraced houses) (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "814)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This feature alone cannot justify the scope of the tax-free extraction of garden areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The limitation of the scope of the tax-free extraction of such areas is primarily in local locations (i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Areas that are not located in the outer area of \u200b\u200ba district in accordance with Section 35 BauGB) of Rhineland-Palatinate are determined by the extent required for future private residential use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to the BFH judgment of August 20, 1997 BStBl 1998 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "17 falls short of a residential property located in a municipality in the Hunsr\u00fcck with almost 1000 inhabitants - with a property size that is customary there - of a total of 784 square meters (of which approx"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "40 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "covered and paved area and approx"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "60 BC"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Garden area) not the size required for single-family houses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In Rhineland-Palatinate, if the farm manager's or senior citizen's apartment affected by the abolition of the value-in-use taxation is in a local location, it can be assumed that a garden area of \u200b\u200bmore than just slightly over 1000 square meters does not meet the requirement"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Example: In the following, the consequences of the elimination of the value-in-use taxation for a farm in a local location with a plot of 2400 sqm are shown:"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Distance area 300 sqm 300 sqm overbuilt area of \u200b\u200bthe farm buildings incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Distance area 700 sqm 700 sqm common driveway and courtyard area (serves more than 10 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "operational purposes) 150 sqm 150 sqm vegetable garden (not independently buildable) 750 sqm 600 sqm 150 sqm (= 1000/1250) (= 250/1250) ornamental garden (neither independent nor can be used for other purposes) 500 sqm 400 sqm 100 sqm (= 1000/1250 ) (= 250/1250) Total 2400 square meters 1300 square meters 250 square meters 850 square meters The areas of the vegetable garden and the ornamental garden total 1250 square meters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "However, only 1000 square meters are tax-free"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Modification: If the ornamental garden is an independent plot of land that can be built on, or if it can be used for another purpose in the foreseeable future, the following result arises in relation to this part of the plot and the total of the areas allocated in each case: Uses total area private assets business assets tax-free, taxable vegetable garden (not independently buildable) 750 sqm 750 sqm ornamental garden (independent (= own parcel) and buildable property) 500 sqm 500 sqm total for the modified example 2400 sqm 1050 sqm 500 sqm 850 sqm modification: If the ornamental garden is an independent and only 150 sqm plot that is not - not even together with other neighboring ones Partial areas - can be used for another use, results in the following: Uses total area private assets business assets tax-free taxable vegetable garden (not independently buildable) 750 sqm 750 sqm ornamental garden (independent (= own parcel) but not otherwise usable property) 150 sqm 150 sqm total for the modified example 2050 sqm 1200 sqm 850 sqm 843 residential building is partly rented and / or partly used for business purposes in addition to private residential use (e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Office space) For the allocation of property areas of a yard to a mixed-use building, the above, for residential use of the operations manager or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Elderly made statements accordingly"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Insofar as the land areas are to be assigned to the residential building, it must be decided how these areas are allocated to the different uses"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The use must be examined separately for each objectively definable area"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Areas that are at least 90 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "serve a specific use, this must be assigned"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If, on the other hand, land areas serve the building as a whole, they are to be divided according to the ratio that corresponds to the division of the building according to the ratio of the usable areas"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Only the share of the area associated with the apartment, which falls under the transitional regulation of Section 52 (15) EStG, can be withdrawn tax-free if the value-in-use taxation is no longer applicable"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Example: The residential building listed below, located on a courtyard property and treated in full as business assets, has two apartments of the same size (manager's apartment and rented apartment); 1420 square meters of land are to be added to it"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A separate room in the operations manager's apartment (10 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "this apartment) is used as an office"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The elimination of the value-in-use taxation results in the following effects: Uses Total area Land attributable to other use (= still business assets) Land attributable to owner-occupied apartment (= tax-free withdrawal) Built-up area of \u200b\u200bthe residential building incl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "300 square meters of which are allocated to the apartments 150 square meters (= 50 percent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") 135 sqm (= 45 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") and the office (10 BC)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "of the works manager's apartment) 15 sqm (= 5%"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") separate access to the residential building 60 sqm 33 sqm (= 55 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") 27 sqm (= 45 v"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ") Front garden 100 sqm 55 sqm 45 sqm rented garage 30 sqm 30 sqm garage for your own, privately used car 30 sqm 30 sqm vegetable garden (exclusive own use) 400 sqm 400 sqm lawn (shared by tenants) 500 sqm 50 sqm 250 sqm total 1420 sqm 533 sqm 887 sqm the areas of the vegetable garden and the lawns are to be allocated according to their actual use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "85 Diagram for determining the tax-free extractable land As Appendix 3, I have attached a simplified diagram for determining the tax-free extractable land belonging to the home of an operations manager and / or senior citizen"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "86 Examination of the information provided by the taxpayer After receipt of a declaration from the taxpayer regarding the discontinuation of the value-in-use taxation pursuant to Section 52 (15) EStG for an apartment belonging to agricultural and forestry business assets, no later than when the assessment is carried out for the assessment period affected by the application (see no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "822) to determine whether the taxpayer has provided the information required for the application of Section 52 (15) EStG on the location, type, use and size of the apartment and on the location and size of the associated land"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If this information is missing or incomplete, the missing information must be obtained from the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The form (ESt CH 2) attached as Annex 4, developed by OFD Hanover, can be used for this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The form has been forwarded to the tax offices in the amount of an estimated need"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "A corresponding national form is currently being developed; it is planned as an annex to Annex L of the 1998 income tax return"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the event of doubts about the size of the property declared as tax-free by the taxpayer due to the individual situation, the official agricultural expert (ALS) must be called in to determine the facts"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Involving the ALS to review the facts of the matter can be omitted, for example, if an external audit is to be expected in the foreseeable future"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "During the site visit, the ALS only has to record or"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "To make determinations on the information provided by the taxpayer"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The legal assessment of the established facts is the responsibility of the responsible assessment department"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For the taxable area to be withdrawn, the ALS - if necessary"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "in consultation with the building surveyor - determine the partial value"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "87 Elimination of the value-in-use taxation in legally assessed cases 871 Recording of the extraction profit in old cases"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of 4 6 1997 no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "8, the extraction of that part of the land belonging to the apartment that exceeds the required and customary extent leads to a taxable extraction profit in the financial year of extraction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "As far as according to the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Minutes of the ESt group meeting on August 22, 1988, Part V No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "12 the opinion has been taken that the extent of the land belonging to the dwelling will only be decided at the time of the actual removal or sale of the residential property, this can no longer be adhered to"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In this respect, according to the principles of the BFH judgment of 24 10 1996 BStBl 1997 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "50 taxable removal of the associated land, which exceeds the required and customary scope, can no longer be made up in cases that have been assessed as final"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "872 Effect of the original application for the discontinuation of the value in use taxation However, if the taxpayer incorrectly assigned parts of the property of the tax-free apartment to be withdrawn to his original application for the cessation of the value in use taxation, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Areas that are more than 10 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "were used for business purposes or were not intended for permanent private use, business assets can regularly be assumed in this respect"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If a (taxable) extraction would have been permissible for such property areas clearly identified in the application at this point in time, no effective, i. E"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "clear and unmistakable withdrawal action with the intention of uncovering the hidden reserves (see BFH judgment of 16 3 1983 BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "459, 462 f"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "for writing off an asset with no profit effect)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For this come z"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "unused, but not areas that are more than 50 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "are used operationally in question"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "9 Validity of the substitute economic value when applying Section 7g of the Income Tax Act (EStG) In the new federal states, in accordance with Section 125 (2) BewG, substitute economic values \u200b\u200bare used for taxation instead of the standard values \u200b\u200bfor farms in agriculture and forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The formation of the substitute economic value - unlike the determination of the unit value - is based on a usage unit in which all agricultural and forestry assets regularly used by the same person (user) are included, even if the user is not the owner"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to Section 126 (2) BewG, for taxes other than real estate tax, the equivalent economic value or a corresponding proportion of this value is to be applied to the person to which agricultural and forestry assets are to be allocated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The ownership structure and the share of the substitute economic value are to be determined in the assessment process of the respective tax"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For the application of Section 7g (2) No. 1 EStG in the acceding area, Section 57 (3) EStG stipulates that instead of the decisive unit value of the agricultural and forestry business and the values \u200b\u200bshown therein, the substitute economic value according to Section 125 BewG is to be assumed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "It is questionable whether, when applying \u00a7 7g EStG, the substitute economic value is use-related, i.e."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "without changes, to be added or to be converted according to ownership"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "I ask you to take the view that for the application of \u00a7 7g EStG the equivalent economic value has to be converted according to the ownership structure"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "10 Lease of hunting areas 101 General According to Section 13 Paragraph 1 No. 3 EStG, income from hunting is included in income from agriculture and forestry if it is related to the operation of agriculture or forestry"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to the highest court rulings, this connection exists if the farmer's and forestry's hunt serves his own agricultural and forestry operations in such a way that it benefits the agricultural and forestry areas of the operation (BFH judgment of 13 7 1978 BStBl II 1979 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "100)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "If this is missing (below under no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "102-104) context, the expenses incurred by hunting cannot be deducted as operating expenses of the agricultural and forestry business"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "102 Own hunting district If the farmer and forester practices the hunt himself in a private hunting district, such an operational connection is readily affirmed"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "103 Own areas are not sufficient for the formation of an own hunting district"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "to differentiate between two groups of cases if the farmer and forester leases the hunting district or part thereof"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to this, the operational connection is affirmed on the basis of a flat-rate and purely area-related regulation, if the hunting areas of the district predominantly consist of property used by the farmer and forestry owner or, in the case of several tenants, they have divided up the district under civil law in such a way that those assigned to the taxpayer are assigned Compose areas predominantly from property used by the company itself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "According to the BFH judgment of 11 7 1996 BFH / NV 1997 p, the connection between leasing for private hunting and the agricultural and forestry operations is"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "103, on the other hand, only if the leasing takes place for compelling reasons under public law or the leasing is necessary for the proper management of the agricultural and forestry operation concerned or the leased areas are mainly used by the company itself"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The under no"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "103 listed, for the allocation of leased hunting areas to the agricultural and forestry operations, the general regulation according to area shares is to be applied separately to these leased areas when leasing hunting areas to an existing own hunting district; the hunting grounds are not included in the ratio calculation"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "11 Withdrawal of business goods from business assets through change of use before 1 7 1979 According to the BMF letter of 15 3 1979 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "162 and from 28 7 1983 BStBl I S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "383, under the conditions specified there, a change in the use of business assets in non-bookkeeping operations could lead to a withdrawal without profit realization if the change in use was carried out before 1 7 1979"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "With judgments of 4 11 1982 BStBl 1983 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "448, from 7 11 1996 BStBl 1997 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "245 and from 15 5 1997 BFH / NV 1997 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In 850 the BFH decided that these administrative regulations lack a legal basis"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In the opinion of the BFH, the assets in question remained business assets until they were actually removed or sold, even if the taxpayer assumed a compulsory withdrawal based on the administrative regulations and accordingly treated the assets as private assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "At the federal level, it is currently being examined what consequences this case law will have for the continued existence of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Administrative instructions of 15 3 1979 and 28 7 1983 result"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Therefore, I would ask you not to finally process individual cases in which the application of these administrative regulations is important until further instructions are issued"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "This can be the case with the sale, free transfer or development of a piece of business property that was treated as private property in the past without realizing a withdrawal profit"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The same applies to operational tasks if such a property is available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Of the aforementioned administrative instructions are u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The following cases, which existed up to 1 7 1979, are not included: Leasing of a business as a whole without a declaration of closure (cf."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of 28 7 1983 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "); (mere) cessation of use or closure of the property area (see the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "BMF letter of 28 7 1983 a"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "); short-term leasing (= change of use) of land or parts of land, e.g."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "for one to two financial years; mdl"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Lease agreement concluded, because a land lease agreement concluded before July 1, 1986, required the written form if it was concluded for a period longer than one year (cf. \u00a7 219 EGBGB, inserted by the law of 8 11 1985 on the reorganization of agricultural lease law, Federal Law Gazette I p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "2065 2071 Article 2 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "V with \u00a7 581 and \u00a7 566 BGB in the version valid until July 1, 1986); lease agreement concluded for an unlimited period, because such a land lease agreement concluded before July 1, 1986 could be terminated at the end of each lease year (\u00a7 595 BGB in the version valid until July 1, 1986) 1986 version); mutual or ring leasing of land (see Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "from 20 6 1996 - S-2230 A - St 34 2 -, No."}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the administrative instructions are no longer relevant if a property was used for own business after 30 6 1979"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The taxpayer has to prove that all requirements for the application of the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Administrative regulations are met in his case"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "Existing doubts are at his expense"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The decision can only be postponed if, in individual cases, a comprehensive description of the facts and submission of the relevant documents has proven that the aforementioned administrative instructions are relevant"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "12 Admission of the annual Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "for the income taxation of the non-bookkeeping farmers and the estimation of farmers in the income tax card The annual Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "for the income taxation of the non-bookkeeping farmers (fruit and vegetable growing as well as winegrowing businesses) and the valuation farmers have so far been included in the income tax index with the same content (cards 8 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": ", 9 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "and 10 ff"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "to \u00a7 13 EStG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The distributors for the aforementioned Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "and Kartei-Vfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "are comparable; with the distributor of the Kartei-Vfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "no additional agents are recorded"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "In addition, the Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "and Kartei-Vfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "made available in the full word search system FINDEX"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "The annual Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "For administrative and economic reasons, the income taxation of the farmers addressed here will no longer be published twice in paper form with immediate effect; the inclusion of this Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "in the income tax file is therefore omitted"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "At the next opportunity, all of the annual Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "singled out for income taxation of farmers and foresters"}, {"meta": {"name": "0165369.xml"}, "text": "--- Income tax / wage tax / church tax Rhineland-Palatinate Agriculture Kw / 98/28"}]